space.arim.api.util.collect

Class FunctionalMap<K,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • space.arim.api.util.collect.FunctionalMap<K,V>
  • Type Parameters:
    K - the key type
    V - the value type
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Map<K,V>, UnmodifiableByDefaultMap<K,V>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    CalculationMap

    public class FunctionalMap<K,V>
extends Object
implements UnmodifiableByDefaultMap<K,V>
    Represents a map which takes arbitrary keys and maps them dynamically to a value when get(Object) is called.

    Principles:
    1 Any object of the correct key type is a valid key. The key set is therefore unbounded.
    2 The mapped values cannot be computed in the aggregate because the key set is infinite; the values collection is thus undefined.
    3 An entry is contained within the map if the entry key maps to the entry value.
    4 Infinity cannot be reduced in number or size. Subtraction has no effect.

    The specifications follow from the principles.
    Specifications:
    * The map is presumed to have an infinite key set. keySet() returns an InfinitySet. (principle 1)
    * size() returns Integer.MAX_VALUE and isEmpty() returns false. (principle 1)
    * instanceCheck(Object) is used to check the type of key objects, as a workaround * containsKey(Object) returns true if and only if the key object is valid. (principle 1)
    * get(Object) will return a mapped result, as specified by a mapping function provided at construction, for any valid key. (principle 1)
    * keySet() returns an InfinitySet. (principle 1)
    * containsValue(Object) always returns false. (principle 2)
    * values() returns an empty immutable collection. (principle 2)
    * entrySet() returns a special set, see FunctionalMapEntrySet for details. (principle 3)
    * The map's modification methods all throw UnsupportedOperationException. (principle 4)
    Author:
    A248

      • FunctionalMap

        public FunctionalMap(Function<K,V> mappingFunction,
                     Predicate<Object> keyInstanceCheck)
        Creates a map based on the given mapping function and instanceof check.
        The function used is when get(Object) is called. Note that #get() may be called internally.
        The instance checking predicate should return truthfully, or programmers will endure ClassCastException.
        Parameters:
        mappingFunction - the mapping function
        keyInstanceCheck - used to evaluate whether a key object is of the correct type
